### 5. Apply repo documentation rules

Re-read the documentation-updates section of the repo's `CLAUDE.md` and apply every rule it specifies (typical rules: update a feature doc, update conventions if you introduced a new pattern, record an ADR for architectural decisions).

### 6. Report

- Files created — one-line purpose each
- Files modified — one-line summary of the change
- FR/EC coverage map — which code path enforces each requirement
